Maintainer: Zhenke Wu <zhenkewu@umich.edu>
Description: This package implememnts fast algorithms to fit structured latent class models (SLAM)
    for high-dimensional dependent binary data (Gu and Xu, 2019,'JMLR'). SLAMs are a special family of 
    discrete latent variable models widely used in social and biological sciences. The goal is to learn from high-dimensional data the 
    signiﬁcant attribute patterns based on a SLAM with potentially high-dimensional conﬁgurations of the latent attributes.
    The algorithms perform selection of the attribute patterns, estimation of the unknown Q-matrix connecting the measurements to the latent attributes, 
    and other model parametersincluding proportion parameters and response probability parameters.
